\mathbf{P}
M_{2\times2}=\bigl(\begin{smallmatrix}x &0 \\ 0 & y\end{smallmatrix}\bigr)
x,y\in\mathbb{R}
P
P_{2\times 2}=\left(\begin{matrix}a &b \\ c & d\end{matrix}\right)
\left(\begin{matrix}y &0 \\ 0 & x\end{matrix}\right)=\frac{1}{\det (P)}\left(\begin{matrix}d &-b \\ -c  & a \\ \end{matrix}\right)\left(\begin{matrix}x &0 \\ 0 & y\end{matrix}\right)\left(\begin{matrix}a &b \\ c & d\end{matrix}\right)
\left(\begin{matrix}(ad-bc)y &0 \\ 0 & (ad-bc)x\end{matrix}\right)=\left(\begin{matrix}d &-b \\ -c  & a \\ \end{matrix}\right)\left(\begin{matrix}x &0 \\ 0 & y\end{matrix}\right)\left(\begin{matrix}a &b \\ c & d\end{matrix}\right)
a,b,c,d
da=db=ca=cb=bc=0
P^{-1}
P
